        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A118"/>
        <p>An <a href="ch60s11.html#MonstersIntro-A117">assassin vine</a> uses simple tactics:</p>
        <p>It lies still until prey comes within reach, then attacks. It uses its entangle ability both to catch prey and to deter counterattacks.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1640508"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A119"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Constrict (Ex):</strong></span> An <a href="ch60s11.html#MonstersIntro-A117">assassin vine</a> deals 1d6+7 points of damage with a successful grapple check.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1640547"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A120"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Entangle (Su):</strong></span> An <a href="ch60s11.html#MonstersIntro-A117">assassin vine</a> can animate plants within 30 feet of itself as a free action (Ref DC 13 partial).</p>
          <p>The effect lasts until the vine dies or decides to end it (also a free action). The save DC is Wisdom-based. The ability is otherwise similar to <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E66">entangle</a></em></span> (caster level 4th).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1640603"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A121"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Improved Grab (Ex):</strong></span> To use this ability, an <a href="ch60s11.html#MonstersIntro-A117">assassin vine</a> must hit with its slam attack.</p>
          <p>It can then attempt to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity.</p>
          <p>If it wins the grapple check, it establishes a hold and can constrict.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1640650"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A122"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Blindsight (Ex):</strong></span> <a href="ch60s11.html#MonstersIntro-A117">Assassin vines</a> have no visual organs but can ascertain all foes within 30 feet using sound, scent, and vibration.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1640690"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A123"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Camouflage (Ex):</strong></span> Since an <a href="ch60s11.html#MonstersIntro-A117">assassin vine</a> looks like a normal plant when at rest, it takes a DC 20 <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills294">Spot</a> check to notice it before it attacks.</p>
          <p>Anyone with ranks in <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills303">Survival</a> or <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills197">Knowledge</a> (nature) can use one of those skills instead of <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills294">Spot</a> to notice the plant. <a href="ch64s06.html#MonstersDr-Dw218">Dwarves</a> can use stonecunning to notice the subterranean version.</p>
